<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8963&amp;p=94922#p94922"><![CDATA[
1. While most pages call the bit 6 and 7 of $4000/4004 as duty, the length counter page calls them sequence.<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Length_Counter" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Length_Counter</a><br /><br />2. I followed the APU Sweep page and completely missed the point that<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />A NES APU sweep unit can be made to periodically adjust a pulse channel's period up or down.<br /></div> means the reload flag will be set periodically. I suggest mentioning this fact in the main text below.<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Sweep" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Sweep</a><br /><br />3. Add frame counter to the flow charts. Having 1 starting point in a flow chart makes it easier to follow.<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Pulse" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Pulse</a><br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Triangle" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Triangle</a><br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Noise" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Noise</a><br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC</a><br /><br />Thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4883">mkwong98</a> — Fri Jun 01, 2012 6:34 pm</p><hr />
